<item>
            <title>[LU-18310] parallel-scale-nfsv4 test_metabench: No space left on device</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18310</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;adilger@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/495acc8b-ba64-4b86-a856-a873da5ec286&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/495acc8b-ba64-4b86-a856-a873da5ec286&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/452d1b80-f656-4a80-b893-d3c2382ccbad&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/452d1b80-f656-4a80-b893-d3c2382ccbad&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;test_metabench failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[08/24/2023 17:15:30] Leaving time_file_creation with proc_id = 7
totfile    tot time   create rate   interval   intv time     intv rate
=======  ==========  ============   ========  ==========  ============
   1000     32.3700         30.89       1000     32.3700         30.89
   2000     63.7400         31.38       1000     31.3700         31.88
   3000    100.4090         29.88       1000     36.6690         27.27
   4000    136.2740         29.35       1000     35.8650         27.88
   5000    170.7300         29.29       1000     34.4560         29.02
   6000    204.9140         29.28       1000     34.1840         29.25
   7000    244.4280         28.64       1000     39.5140         25.31
   8000    280.8720         28.48       1000     36.4440         27.44
   9000    318.2790         28.28       1000     37.4070         26.73
  10000    355.4810         28.13       1000     37.2020         26.88

[08/24/2023 17:15:30] Entering par_create_multidir to create 1429 files in 1 dirs
[08/24/2023 17:15:43] FATAL error on process 5
Proc 5: Could not create file number [788] named [VBqEA2OF1cLsZN]: No space left on device
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Test session details:&lt;br/&gt;
clients: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4455&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4455&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-477.15.1.el8_8.x86_64&lt;br/&gt;
servers: &lt;a href=&quot;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4455&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://build.whamcloud.com/job/lustre-master/4455&lt;/a&gt; - 4.18.0-477.15.1.el8_lustre.x86_64&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It looks like this has been failing for a long time (at least since 2023-04-01 when I stopped looking) but no ticket has been filed for it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This may be fallout from a previous test not cleaning up the files, so it would be useful to run &quot;lfs df&quot; and &quot;lfs df -i&quot; to this subtest if it fails to see if the filesystem is actually full, or if there is some other issue.&lt;/p&gt;






&lt;p&gt;VVVVVVV DO NOT REMOVE LINES BELOW, Added by Maloo for auto-association VVVVVVV&lt;br/&gt;
parallel-scale-nfsv4 test_metabench - metabench failed! 1&lt;/p&gt;</description>
